SOC Inventory Automation
========================

soc_inventory/
│
├── config/                         ← EDIT THESE — never touch the Python files for client changes
│   ├── playbook.yaml               ← clients · sites · tools · which Prefect block per tool
│   └── field_map.yaml              ← tool applicability · match keys · Netbox custom field mapping
│
├── runner/                         ← engine — do not edit unless changing core behaviour
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── netbox_client.py            ← queries Netbox, matches devices, PATCHes custom fields
│   ├── field_map_loader.py         ← reads field_map.yaml, answers applicability questions
│   ├── run_task.py                 ← one Prefect task = one client/site/tool combination
│   ├── orphan_collector.py         ← accumulates unmatched records across all tasks
│   └── orphan_report.py            ← generates HTML + CSV orphan report
│
├── flows/                          ← Prefect flow definitions
│   ├── __init__.py
│   └── soc_inventory_flow.py       ← master flow: load playbook → dispatch tasks → report
│
├── scripts/                        ← one file per tool — ONLY file you add when onboarding a new tool
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── ad_inventory.py             ← DONE
│   ├── trellix_inventory.py        ← DONE
│   ├── wsus_inventory.py           ← PENDING
│   ├── wazuh_inventory.py          ← PENDING
│   ├── elastic_inventory.py        ← PENDING
│   ├── nessus_inventory.py         ← PENDING
│   ├── fortigate_inventory.py      ← PENDING
│   ├── vcenter_inventory.py        ← PENDING
│   ├── glpi_inventory.py           ← PENDING
│   ├── teramind_inventory.py       ← PENDING
│   └── mdm_inventory.py            ← PENDING
│
├── tests/                          ← standalone test scripts (no Prefect needed)
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── test_trellix.py             ← DONE
│   └── test_<tool>.py              ← add one per script before wiring into Prefect
│
├── reports/                        ← orphan reports saved here after each run
│   └── (generated at runtime)
│
├── playbook_loader.py              ← reads playbook.yaml → flat list of ResolvedTask objects
├── create_blocks.py                ← one-time: register all credentials in Prefect vault
├── prefect.yaml                    ← deployment config: schedules, work pool, parameters
├── requirements.txt                ← Python dependencies
├── SETUP.sh                        ← step-by-step Prefect on-premise setup guide
└── README                          ← this file

SCRIPT CONTRACT
---------------
Every script in scripts/ must expose exactly:

    async def fetch(credentials: dict, **params) -> dict[str, dict]

- keyed by hostname (lowercased, no domain suffix)
- values must contain the keys defined in field_map.yaml fields: section
- return None for fields you cannot populate — runner skips nulls
- no Netbox imports, no client logic, no hardcoded values

ADDING A NEW CLIENT
-------------------
1. Add tenant + sites to Netbox (slugs must match what you put in playbook)
2. Add entry to config/playbook.yaml
3. Add credential blocks to create_blocks.py and run it
4. prefect deploy --all
→ next run picks it up automatically

ADDING A NEW TOOL
-----------------
1. Write scripts/{tool}_inventory.py
2. Write tests/test_{tool}.py — verify it works without Prefect
3. Add tool entry to config/field_map.yaml
4. Register in runner/run_task.py SCRIPT_REGISTRY dict
5. Add to relevant sites in config/playbook.yaml
6. Add credential blocks to create_blocks.py and run it
7. prefect deploy --all
